The utility says the extensive use of heating appliances is likely to cause power cuts. JOHANNESBURG - City Power says it's expecting sporadic power outages across the city of Johannesburg due to the forecasted cold snap over this weekend.The utility says the extensive use of heating appliances is likely to cause power cuts.It s urging consumers to save energy and minimise equipment failure by using gas, oil or infrared heaters, solar heating and dressing warmly.City Power 's Virgil James says: We understand that it s cold. Try to dress warmly, stay indoors or use a fleece blanket where possible. It's merely an appeal as we know it s not possible to stay without heat in a house. The appeal is that you need to save energy over this weekend to avoid an overload on the network. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)